---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Guides | burninjurycalc.com';
const description = 'In-depth guides to burn injury compensation, classifications and prognosis, post-burn practical steps, and common claim misconceptions.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Guides</h1>

  <p>In-depth, plain-language guides covering the major topics in burn-injury claims. Each is written and reviewed by our editorial team and includes citations to primary sources.</p>

  <h2>The four core guides</h2>

  <h3><a href="/guides/how-burn-injury-settlements-are-calculated">How Burn Injury Settlements Are Calculated</a></h3>
  <p>A detailed walkthrough of the damages categories used in burn cases, life-care planning for iterative reconstructive surgery, economic-loss analysis, disfigurement valuation, and jurisdictional adjustments. Includes worked examples for moderate scald and severe defective-product fire cases.</p>

  <h3><a href="/guides/burn-classifications-and-prognosis">Burn Classifications and Prognosis</a></h3>
  <p>The medical classification system: depth (1st through 4th degree), Total Body Surface Area (TBSA) with the Lund-Browder chart and Rule of Nines, healing patterns, scar evolution over the first 2&ndash;5 years, and prognosis by burn severity.</p>

  <h3><a href="/guides/what-to-do-after-a-burn-injury">What to Do After a Burn Injury</a></h3>
  <p>Step-by-step practical guidance for the days and weeks after a burn: verified burn-center care, evidence preservation (the fire scene, defective product, surveillance footage), photographing burn progression for litigation, attorney consultation, and insurance coordination.</p>

  <h3><a href="/guides/common-burn-injury-claim-misconceptions">Common Burn Injury Claim Misconceptions</a></h3>
  <p>Fifteen common misunderstandings about burn-injury compensation &mdash; from settlement timing and disfigurement damages to insurance coverage and tax treatment &mdash; with the actual rules and practical implications.</p>

  <h2>Related references</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/case-types">Burn types and common cause categories</a> &mdash; deeper detail on depth, TBSA, and the typical accident patterns.</li>
    <li><a href="/methodology">Calculator methodology</a> &mdash; the math behind our settlement-range estimator.</li>
    <li><a href="/editorial">Editorial team</a> &mdash; who reviews the content.</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
